<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 6:29PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Pondera, southwestern Liberty, and southeastern Toole Counties
through 715 PM MDT...
At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Conrad, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ledger.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
